					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A commentary on the part of the Zohar (Idra raba).</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer Ḳol be-ramah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר קול ברמה</title>
							<note>
								<p>Contains the commentary on Idra raba (part of the Zohar) based on comments of Isaac Luria, with additions by Ḥayim Vital, Benyamin ha-Kohen and others, and edited by Jacob Ẓemaḥ. </p>
								<p>The volume begins with Kelalim, folio 4r; then follows the commentary itself, folio 9r. An index to the commentary is given on folios 149r-150r. </p>
								<p>Appended are two sections (also bearing on the subject of Idra raba), wntitled Derushe ha-melakhim. These sections are followed by a piece on Beḥinat histalkut, folio 155v.</p>
								<p>See further Scholem, <ref target="Kiryat_Sefer" type="number">26</ref>, pp. 189-194 and <ref target="Avivi_2008" type="page">661</ref>  of vol. 2.</p>
							</note>
							<locus from="1r" to="151v"/>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/18664254">Ẓemaḥ, Jacob ben Ḥayyim, active 17th century</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/18664254">צמח, יעקב בן חיים</persName>
							</author>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Kol_beramah_1785"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
